{"cursor":"22135","size":15,"audio":["http://www.creeca.wisc.edu/resources/lectures/beissingerlunch091407.mp3"],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Ethnic group |group = Roma in Romania Romi |image = |poptime =\nCensus: 621,573 {{cite web |url=http://www.recensamantromania.ro/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/REZULTATE-\nDEFINITIVE-RPL_2011.pdf |title=Romanian 2011 census |publisher=www.edrc.ro |accessdate=2011-12-\n10 |last= |first= }}  |popplace = Central, south and West Romania |rels =\nRomanian Orthodox Church, Roman Catholicism and Pentecostalism |langs =\nmainly Romani (60%) and Romanian (40%) |related = }}\n\n\n\n\n\nThe '[[Romani people|Roma]]' (Roma in Romani; Romi or Èigani in Romanian)\nconstitute one of the largest minorities in Romania. According to the 2011\ncensus, they number 621,573 people or 3.3% of the total population, being the\nsecond-largest ethnic minority in Romania after Hungarians. The Roma are Romania's most socially and economically\ndisadvantaged minority, with high illiteracy levels. [http://web.archive.or-\ng/web/20110720095738/http://www.anr.gov.ro/docs/statistici/Public_policies_for_-\nRoma_in_Romania_2000_2005_190.pdf Public policies for Roma in Romania,\n2000â2005: legislative framework, institutions, programmes, achievements and\nexpectations]. anr.gov.ro [http://www.nzz.ch/nachrichten/schweiz/ruma-\nenien_sieht_ende_starker_auswanderung_1.698521.html RumÃ¤nien sieht Ende starker\nAuswanderung (Schweiz, NZZ Online)]. Nzz.ch. Retrieved on 2012-01-\n15. Beth, Mary. (2005-02-10) [http://www.usatoday.com/news/world/2005-02-01-roma-\neurope_x.htm European effort spotlights plight of the Roma]. Usatoday.com.\nRetrieved on 2012-01-\n15. [http://www.migrationinformation.org/Feature/display.cfm?id=308\nThe Roma of Eastern Europe: Still Searching for Inclusion].\nMigrationinformation.org. Retrieved on 2012-01-15.\n\nDocumenting Romania's Roma population remains difficult; many Roma do not\ndeclare their ethnicity in the census and do not have an identity card or\nbirth certificate.  Since 2007 members of this ethnic group have\nmigrated to Spain, Italy, and France, where many Roma have experienced\nhostility and racism.\n","linknr":581,"url":"Roma_minority_in_Romania","recorded":1374859398,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Roma_in_Romania&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Roma_in_Romania&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Roma_in_Romania","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Roma_minority_in_Romania&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Flag_of_Romania.svg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Flag_of_Romania.svg/80px-Flag_of_Romania.svg.png","/wiki/File:Roma_flag.svg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Roma_flag.svg/80px-Roma_flag.svg.png","#cite_note-CensusRef-1","/wiki/Romani_language","/wiki/Romanian_language","/wiki/Romanian_Orthodox_Church","/wiki/Roman_Catholicism","/wiki/Pentecostal_Union_of_Romania","/wiki/Category:Romani","/wiki/Romani_people","/wiki/File:Roma_flag.svg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Roma_flag.svg/60px-Roma_flag.svg.png","/wiki/Romani_society_and_culture","/wiki/Romani_music","/wiki/Romani_language","/wiki/History_of_the_Romani_people","/wiki/Romani_dance","/wiki/Romani_people#r